Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba is due to meet with business leaders to formulate strategies to counter the recession. CAPE TOWN - Cabinet is calling on business and labour to partner with government to intensify growth and improve confidence in the economy.Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba is due to meet with business leaders to formulate strategies to counter the recession.Briefing the media on Cabinet decisions, Communications Minister Ayanda Dlodlo said Gigaba has been given the go-ahead to announce interventions aimed at turning the economy around.Cabinet has been briefed by Gigaba on the latest GDP figures, which saw a contraction of 0.7% in the first quarter and plunged South Africa into its second recession since 2009.Communications Minister Ayanda Dlodlo says there are sectors of the economy that can be leveraged to boost growth. Cabinet reiterates that South Africans must continue to act in unison, especially during difficult times, and work even harder to ensure that the country reclaims its investment grade status. Cabinet has also noted the appointment of Dondo Mogajane as the new director-general of the Finance Ministry. Mogajane is a long-standing deputy director general in the department.He replaces Lungisa Fuzile who resigned in the wake of the axing of former finance minister Pravin Gordhan. (Edited by Zinhle Nkosi)